e constitution of an absolute Enemy through the suggestion of conspiracy, of a world turned upside-down, or the figure of Satan.Rogozinski locates one of the origins of the witch-hunt in the anguish that popular uprisings arouse in dominant classes. The second part of the book extends the investigation to related phenomena, such as the extermination of lepers in the Middle Ages and the Reign of Terror during the French Revolution. By studying these historical experiences and marking their differences and similarities, this book shows the passage from exclusion to persecution and how revolts of the oppressed can let themselves be transformed and captured by persecutory politics. The analyses presented thus shed light on conspiracy theory and the terror apparatuses of our time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHate2DLC. 0aHate. 0aPersecutionzEuropexHistory2DLC. 0aPersecutionzEuropexHistory. 0aPolitical persecutionzEuropexHistory2DLC. 0aPolitical persecutionzEuropexHistory. 0aWitch huntingzEuropexHistory2DLC. 0aWitch huntingzEuropexHistory. 4aHistory. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aRenaissance Studies. 7aHISTORY / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aapparatuses.  aconfession.  ademonization.  aexclusion.  ahatred.  apersecution.  arevolution.  aschemes stigma.  aterror.  atorture.  awitch-hunt.1 aGinzburg, Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRazavi, Sepehr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRogozinski, Jacob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311075168040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531505387?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531505387423Coveruhtt